    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-11T17:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-11T17:28:00-05:00" n="728"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/7–1152: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d728fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi (priority), London, and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-11T18:28:00-04:00"
                            >July 11, 1952—6:28 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>104. While <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> realizes <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>’s remarks (<gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss> 155)<note n="2" xml:id="d728fn2">
                        <ref target="#d727">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> probably constitute rejection <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> proposals, it is not clear whether <persName corresp="#p_NJ1"
                        >Nehru</persName> gave you a specific answer to transmit Karachi. If
                        <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> authd you transmit substance of
                    his remarks to Karachi <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> assumes your
                    approach is terminated and <persName corresp="#p_WAM1">Warren</persName> may now
                    convey <gloss target="#t_msg1">msg</gloss> to <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>.
                    On other hand if <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> did not
                    specifically indicate reply to be transmitted <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> suggests in your discretion you see <persName corresp="#p_NJ1"
                        >Nehru</persName> again and ask him what he wld like you to report back to
                    Karachi. While this may not affect his apparent position it will serve purpose
                    impressing further upon him seriousness his failure respond to a generous offer.
                    Likewise in view great importance these talks it is essential record be clear.
                    As you aware <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> not expected proceed
                    with his negots until such time as your approach completed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
